description:
src/sanitize.rs sanitize_html() (lines 6-34) allocates a new HashSet<&str> of allowed tags and a new HashMap of tag attributes on every invocation. These are static configuration that never changes.

What goes wrong: unnecessary allocation on every post creation, feed poll entry, webhook payload, and outbox page render. Not a hot-path crisis but a gratuitous waste in a function called frequently.

Fix: use LazyLock (already used in content.rs) to build the ammonia::Builder once:

static SANITIZER: LazyLock<ammonia::Builder<'static>> = LazyLock::new(|| {
    let tags: HashSet<&str> = [...].into();
    let mut attrs = HashMap::new();
    attrs.insert("a", ["href"].into_iter().collect());
    let mut b = Builder::new();
    b.tags(tags).tag_attributes(attrs);
    b
});

Then sanitize_html becomes: SANITIZER.clean(html).to_string()
